<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-128-276  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 128 276.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Oct 16 1989 v3 n42 p10(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Army command seeks land-based anti-satellite weapons system.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poos, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Army's Strategic Defense Command (SDC) plans to issue a draftrequest for proposals in early Oct 1989 for an anti-satellite(Asat) weapons system that would be based on land.andP;  Thekinetic-energy system must be capable of non-nuclear destructionof military satellites.andP;  The procurement is part of a nationalplan that includes surveillance sensors, control andcommunications elements, and both kinetic- and direct-energyweapons.andP;  The project will use information that was gathered inthe Army Zeus and Air Force Thor anti-satellite programs of the1960s and 1970s, according to the SDC.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SatellitesDefense ContractsWeaponsProgramsUnited States. Army. Strategic Defense CommandRequest for Proposals.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>